Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Company 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, inspected a reconnoitering company of KPA Unit 720.
 After receiving a salute, he watched its servicemen in training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled to increase the combat capability of the company, greatly satisfied to learn that all servicemen of the company have been trained into a-match-for-a-hundred fighters who have acquired admirable combat technique and capability by implementing the WPK's policy of training to the letter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He watched various species of young trees planted by the servicemen in and around the compound of the barracks during the spring tree-planting season and highly praised them for their patriotism, saying those trees would form a thick woodland several decades later. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he went round an educational room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a wash-cum-bath house, a sideline products store, an outdoor resting place and other places of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took measures for providing better living conditions to the soldiers, saying that the company should not let the soldiers standing guard over a post in the remote mountain area have any inconvenience in their living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met with Kim Yong Gil, Ri Yong Jin, Choe Kum Chol and other soldiers who have distinguished themselves in their service and had a warm conversation with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said nothing is more memorable and worthwhile than the days spent by one as a soldier with a rifle in hands, highly praising them for having devoted all their wisdom and energies to their combat and political training, supply service and management of the company with awareness that his faithful service means patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He spared time to watch an art performance given by servicemen of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the servicemen of the company a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle as gifts before having a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su and Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Yong Chol, member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and first vice department director of the C.C., WPK.

Film Show for Military Attaches Corps 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of the People's Armed Forces arranged a film show on Thursday on the occasion of the 73rd anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army.
 Present on invitation were members of the military attaches corps here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA officers were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched the Korean documentary "The Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks". The film shows the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il for developing the KPA into invincible revolutionary armed forces of Juche strong in idea and faith, their warm love for servicepersons and the combat power of the KPA.

KPA Birthday Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- A seminar and a meeting were held in Russia and Sweden respectively on April 8 and 9 to commemorate the Day of the Sun, the 12th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and the 73rd birthday of the Korean People's Army.
 At the seminar Dmitri Kostenko, chairman of the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea, elaborated on the revolutionary exploits of President Kim Il Sung, praising him as a distinguished leader of the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has pursued the Songun politics, wisely leading the revolution and construction with arms, the speaker said, expressing the belief that the DPRK will surely build a great prosperous powerful nation despite the U.S. administration's desperate moves to stifle it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Christer Lundgren, chairman of the Sweden-Korea Friendship Association, said at the meeting that Kim Il Sung had led the revolution and construction, always relying on the strength of the people as required by the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Denouncing the evermore undisguised moves of the Bush administration to isolate and stifle the DPRK, he said that his association would boost the movement for solidarity with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Oceanic Preparatory Committee Inaugurated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Oceanic preparatory committee for the "Meeting Praising the Great Persons of Mt. Paektu" was held at the building of a coal miners union of Australia on April 11.
 The chairman of the Australia-DPRK Association for Friendship and Cultural Exchange and Don Borrie, chairman of the New Zealand-DPRK Society, were elected co-chairmen of the committee at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An executive member of the International Preparatory Committee for the "Meeting Praising the Great Persons of Mt. Paektu" who is the secretary general of the Australian association said in his speech at the ceremony that the meeting will be an important gathering for glorifying the immortal exploits performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu for the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence, referring to their revolutionary lives and immortal feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the preparatory committee would organize colorful functions for friendship and culture on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 A letter to leader Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

U.S. War Moves under Fire in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the Reunification Solidarity, the National People's Solidarity and the Citizens' Solidarity for Peaceful Reunification in south Korea reportedly held a joint press conference in Seoul on April 18 in connection with the evermore undisguised U.S. moves for a war against the north.
 Speakers there demanded the dismantlement of the south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command," holding that all war scenarios reflecting the U.S. hostile policy toward the north be cancelled without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the conference vehemently denounced on behalf of the 70 million fellow countrymen "the OPLAN 5029-05" worked out by the command for military invasion of the north, noting that they could not repress their anger at it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is more serious is that the U.S. troops stationed in south Korea are contemplating the issue of an order for "DEFCON 3" even in case of any sign of "serious internal situation" in the north and in that case the prerogative of command over operations would automatically go over to them to adversely affect the situation on the Korean Peninsula, it noted.

All Koreans Called Upon to Struggle for Withdrawal of U.S. Forces from S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued a statement on April 18 calling upon the 70 million Koreans to drive the U.S. forces out of south Korea without fail on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the historic joint conference of representatives of political parties and public organizations in South and North Korea.
 The joint conference held in Pyongyang was a historic assembly attended by delegates from the south and the north transcending differences in ideology, political view, social system and religious belief to prevent the division of the nation and build a reunified country, the statement said, adding that this was a great exploit recorded in the history of the movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It recalled that the U.S. imperialists and the Syngman Rhee clique committed cruel terrorism and assassination against the participants of the joint conference and, at the same time, carried out the ruinous "separate election," causing the national split, an indelible crime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement underscored the need to strengthen the great unity of the whole nation for making this year a year of independent reunification and pullout of the U.S. forces.

National Seminar on Medical Science Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on medical science was held at the Grand People's Study House Thursday on the 20th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's famous work "On the Further Improvement of the Health Service".
 He in the work clarifies the revolutionary essence of the health service, its position and role, and principles and tasks for its development, thus giving perfect answers to ideological and theoretical problems arising in Juche-oriented health care as a whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the seminar, Prof. and Dr. Choe Chang Sik, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Medical Association, read his paper titled "The great leader Comrade Kim Jong Il's famous work 'On the Further Improvement of the Health Service' is a programmatic work indicating a bright way of developing Juche-oriented health service." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said the tasks and ways Kim Jong Il set forth in the work for hygienic and anti-epidemic work, prevention of diseases, prevention of pollution, hygienic information activity and the section doctor system serve as a programmatic guideline that should be tightly grasped in consolidating and developing the socialist health service system of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then seven papers showing an aspect of the development of  Korean medical science were presented, which included "Studies of time treating method according to rhythmic types in high blood pressure", "Studies of anti-cancer effectiveness of preventive medicine against the recurrence and metastasis of cancer" and "Hygienic studies of influence of yellow sand and measures against it".

Japan's Fabrication of "Results of Examination" of Remains Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Members of the National Association for the Promotion of Japan-Korea Diplomatic Relations denounced Japan's fabrication of "results of examination" of the remains of Megumi Yokota at a meeting held in Tokyo on April 8 to hear a report about their visit to the DPRK.
  General Secretary of the association Haruki Wata warned against the biased reports of Japanese media which connived at a report of the British science magazine Nature. He said the one who examined the remains should appear before the media and give a correct explanation for a solution to the question. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And he said it was highly advisable for Japan to think and act discreetly as regards its moves to distort history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Masashi Kimiya, assistant professor of Tokyo University, lamented that Japan was confusing science and politics in the matter of remains.

GNP's Intrigues to Grab Power Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- If such a traitorous conservative camp as the Grand National Party seized power, the elementary fruits of democracy won in south Korea would be trampled upon, the fascist dictatorship of the past be revived and,  worse still, the June 15 joint declaration be blown up and war holocaust be inflicted upon the Korean Peninsula, says a spokesman for the Korean Student Committee in a statement Thursday.
 Lambasting the current maneuvers of the GNP to rally south Korean young folks around it allegedly to prepare for the 2007 presidential election and 2008 national assembly election, the statement goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Some time ago, the GNP held a caucus meeting and discussed "measures to win the support" of young folks including the present high school and university students who would be voters in those years for victories in the elections. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These moves of the GNP are motivated by its crafty intention to win over the young generation standing in the van of progress and reform of the south Korean society and use them as leverage for the realization of its reactionary intrigues for power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is a group of pro-U.S. flunkeyist traitors of worst type. Down through history, it has suppressed the struggle of the south Korean youth and students for independence, democracy and reunification, crudely trampled upon academic freedom and offered young people as cannon fodder, zealously following the U.S. policy of aggression and war. It is, indeed, a snag in the way of south Korean social progress and the main obstacle to the peace and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean youth and students and people should never be duped by the GNP's appeasement and deception, but determinedly reject its reactionary plot to seize power.

Japanese Reactionaries' Moves to Grab Tok Islet Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Friday in a signed article denounces the Japanese reactionaries' shameless moves to grab Tok Islet
aiming at reinvasion of Korea.
 These moves are a revelation of their criminal design to launch reinvasion of Korea at any cost, availing themselves of the changed situation in the international arena, the article observes, and goes on: The Japanese militarists' moves to seize the islet were prompted by their ulterior aim to provide a military guarantee for the unlimited interests of the Japanese monopoly capitalists that have grown corpulent to the maximum in the 21st century and establish military supremacy in the Asia-Pacific region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By raising a claim to Tok Islet the Japanese reactionaries seek to spark a war of reinvasion of Korea under the pretext of regaining "their land" without being branded as an aggressor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the calculation of Japan that bringing Tok Islet, four southern Kuriles of Russia and Diaoyu Islands of China under its control would help it hold a very favorable military strategic position in Northeast Asia. The Japanese reactionaries, therefore, attach great importance to their operation to grab Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These moves have rendered the situation on the Korean Peninsula tenser and resulted in building a structure of confrontation between the whole of Korea and Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prevailing situation requires all Koreans in the north and the south to shatter the Japanese militarists' moves for reinvasion through national cooperation. If all Koreans in the north, the south and overseas pool their ardent patriotic will, they can deal a deadly blow at the Japanese militarists who run amuck like a puppy knowing no fear of a tiger and force them to stop coveting Korea again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and the people of the DPRK take a serious view of the Japanese reactionaries' moves to grab Tok Islet as part of invasion of the inviolable land of Korea. If they dare spark a war of reinvasion against Korea the army and people of the DPRK will mobilize all military potentials built up so far and deal deadly blows at them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their moves to seize the islet will only drive Japan to a final ruin. They should keep this in mind and stop at once the robber-like moves to grab Tok Islet.

KPA, Champion of Peace
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang April 22 (KCNA) -- The Korean People's Army is celebrating its 73rd birthday on April 25.
 The entire people of the county take this opportunity to look back on the proud history of the heroic army, which has won two wars against the Japanese and U.S. imperialists and has defended peace, frustrating all the moves of the enemies to start another war.
 Far from drawing a serious lesson from their defeat in the war of aggression against the DPRK in the 1950s, the US imperialists have incessantly perpetrated provocations on the ground and the sea and in the air, looking for a chance to invade the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their provocations, however, have been smashed by the KPA with an invincible might.
 Typical of them are the Pueblo incident (1968), EC-121 incident (1969) and Panmunjom incident (1976). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last decade, the KPA has shattered thousands of their grave military provocations to safeguard the security and peace of the country with credit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was in Juche 83 (1994) that an ordinary soldier brought down at a single shot a U.S. high-performance helicopter when it intruded into the territorial air of the DPRK for a spy mission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA has defended the sovereignty of the country and socialism, answering the imperialists' tough stance with tougher measures, undaunted by their continued moves of aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the Songun politics, it is equipped with a powerful war deterrent capable of destroying any new-type weapons and means of operation of the enemies and repulsing their surprise invasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA, under the command of Kim Jong Il, is fully displaying its might as an army strong in ideology and faith and as a matchless army equipped with both modern offensive and defense means.

New Anticancer Medicine Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Researchers of the Pharmaceutical Institute under the Academy of Medical Science of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have developed a new botanical anticancer medicine.
 It contains ingredients extracted from various kinds of rare plants and yew growing on the northern mountainous areas of the country 800-1,000 meters above the sea level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In an interview with KCNA, Dr. Ri Hui Suk, a Merited Scientist, told that the medicine is efficacious for such diseases as metastatic breast cancer, ovary cancer, lymphosarcoma, lung cancer, esophageal cancer and terminal malignant tumor, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its manufacturing method is different from that of other countries in extraction, purification, concentration, separation and re-purification of the ingredients. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new method relies on cheap solvents without the use of highly efficient equipment. It consumes one third of electricity as against the other method while ensuring 95 percent of purity.

Quality Furniture Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Pieces of furniture made by the Yonggwang Furniture Joint Venture Company of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are popular among foreign embassies and missions in Pyongyang and local people for their diversified shapes and kinds and good quality.
 The company is developing the furniture decoration method with the introduction of PVC, a high-tech method in the furniture industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By this method, the company is producing furniture of various patterns and shapes.
 Several hundred pieces of 60 kinds of furniture have found their way to foreign embassies and missions in the DPRK. Some foreigners order them to bring with themselves to their countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its products of more than 200 kinds are highly appreciated at home. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Director of the company Sin Nam Chol told KCNA that his company, with competent technicians, guarantees the quality of products in a scientific and technical way in keeping with the fast-developing trend of furniture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The company also produces plastic sashes, distemper paints, tiles of various sizes, colorful patterns and pictures and sanitaryware. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The distemper paints, made of natural materials, is hardly influenced by ultraviolet and infrared rays, and their quality is guaranteed for 30 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The paints won a gold medal and diploma at the international building materials show held in Shanghai, China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The company, located in Hyongjesan District, Pyongyang, started joint venture with the China National Foreign Trade Import and Export Corporation in Jilin in September Juche 82 (1993).

7th Kimilsungia Festival Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The 7th Kimilsungia Festival which opened on April 13 closed Friday.
 The festival held on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of Kimilsungia, flower representing the sun, and the Day of the Sun was a festival of flowers which expressed profound reverence and extended highest tribute and glory to President Kim Il Sung. It was, at the same time, a grand political festival which fully showed the revolutionary mettle and noble spiritual world of the army and people in the DPRK single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the biggest-ever festival were at least 10,000 potted Kimilsungias and a variety of rare flowers contributed by organs of the armed forces, ministries and national institutions, all provinces of the country, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, working people and school youth and children. Also among the entries were hundreds of potted Kimilsungias reflecting the best wishes of foreign diplomatic missions and missions of international organizations here, a number of friendship bodies, public organizations and individuals of different countries and overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 750,000 servicepersons, working people, school youth and children including senior officials of the Party, the state and the army visited the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was also visited by the diplomatic corps, the military attaches corps and the economic and commercial councilors' corps here, more than a hundred delegations and art troupes of different countries, overseas Korean delegations and foreigners and overseas Koreans on visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony of the festival was held at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition.
 Present there were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Jong Ha Chol and other senior officials, KPA servicepersons, working people, school youth and children and staff members of the Indonesian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony diplomas of the best prize and commemorative cups went to 2 6 units including the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, Kim Song Dok-led Unit and Ri Phung Gil-led Unit of the KPA, Pyongyang City, the Foreign Ministry, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, the Secretariat of the Cabinet, the Ministry of People's Security and the Ministry of Land and Marine Transport. 41 other units were awarded diplomas of the excellent prize and commemorative cups, 17 units diplomas of merit and commemorative cups and the Central Botanical Garden a diploma of technology prize and a commemorative cup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gold, silver and bronze medals went to 30 individual participants in the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a diploma of special prize was conferred upon the Indonesian embassy here, diplomas of the best prize upon the delegation of the organizing committee for the international floriculture exhibition of the Ministry of Agriculture of Thailand and Ri Pyong Sang, chairman of the American Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Association. Diplomas of excellent prize went to Kim Jin Song, son of anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter So Sun Ok in China, and two Chinese residents in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Kwak Pom Gi, who is chairman of the organizing committee of the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Festival, made a closing address.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, inspected KPA Unit 2183.
 He learned about the unit's performance of duty before watching its servicepersons in training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled to intensify the training, noting that only through an effective combat training can soldiers acquire peculiar and superb tactics, high marksmanship, specialized military technique and strong physical bodies and successfully round off the preparations for battles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After acquainting himself with the ideological education of the servicepersons, he praised the unit for having operated the educational room and entertainment facilities built well for the ideological, moral, cultural and aesthetic education of them and established a revolutionary habit of reading among them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Revolutionary literary and art works are an important means for providing the servicepersons with ideological and moral pabulum, he said, underscoring the need for all of them to avidly read revolutionary novels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He appreciated the efforts exerted by the unit, satisfied to learn that it has channeled efforts into its management, sprucing up the inside and outside of the compound of the barracks like a rest home and providing good conditions for its servicepersons' living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met with Jong Myong Sil, Jon Jong Sil and Kim Chol Nam and other soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the days spent by soldiers are a period for dedication and feats as they devote themselves to the Party, the revolution, the country and the people, he warmly encouraged all of them to become excellent soldiers through their faithful military service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After familiarizing himself with how the unit has realized electrification, he was very pleased to see the power station built by itself paying off profusely. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Ri Yong Chol, member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and first vice department director of its Central Committee.
